grp.VoiceGroup.campaigngroup.help: The name of the Cisco Campaign and Enable- Whether this campaign is enable in Cisco or Not and  Whether the dialer is available to call contacts
grp.VoiceGroup.dialingmode.help: The dialing mode to use for the campaign skill groups Valid values are as follows:
grp.VoiceGroup.dialingmode.help1: 1) PredictiveOnly Dialing: The Dialer component determines the number of customers to dial per agent, based on the abandoned rate. The agent must take the call if logged into a campaign skill group.
grp.VoiceGroup.dialingmode.help2: 2) PreviewOnly Dialing: The agent previews customer information on their desktop, and chooses to contact the customer, skip to another customer, or reject the call.
grp.VoiceGroup.dialingmode.help3: 3) ProgressiveOnly Dialing: The administrator specifies a fixed number of lines to dial per agent instead of the Dialer component determining the number of lines. The agent must take the call if logged into a campaign skill group.
grp.VoiceGroup.dialingmode.help4: 4) PreviewDirect Dialing: The Direct Preview mode is similar to the Preview mode, except that the call is automatically placed by the dialer from the agent's phone after the agent accepts. Because the call is initiated from the agent's phone, the agent hears the ringing, and there is no delay when the customer answers. However, in this mode, the agent must deal with answering machines and other results that the Dialer Call Progress Analysis (CPA) normally handles for other campaign dialing modes.
grp.VoiceGroup.timezone.help: The refURL and display name for the selected time zone. The default time zone is UTC (Universal Coordinated Time). The display name is the text that may be displayed in a user interface and can be localized.
grp.VoiceGroup.skillgroupname.help: The name and the refURL of the skill group assigned to the campaign.
grp.VoiceGroup.overflowagents.help: This parameter ensures that at least one extra agent is reserved before the dialer begins dialing for a Progressive campaign. If the parameter is set to 1, at least two agents must be reserved before the dialer begins dialing. Range is 0 to 100. Default is 0.
grp.VoiceGroup.noofivrports.help: The total number of IVR ports allocated for the skill group. This parameter indicates how many ports are available for the dialer to transfer customer calls. Because this value indicates the total number of ports supported by the IVR for the current skill group, multiple skill groups can make transfer to IVR calls. One IVR can also be used to play different messages based on the route point where the contact is transferred. If multiple dialers are associated with the skill group, each dialer dials a fraction of the total number of ports. Default is 0.
grp.VoiceGroup.recordstocache.help: The minimum number of dialing numbers that each dialer caches for each of the Outbound Option skill groups. Range is 1 to 400. Default is 1.
grp.VoiceGroup.linesperagent.help: The number of lines dedicated to each agent in the campaign. Range is 1 to 100. Default is 2. This parameter performs as follows in the Outbound Option dialing modes:
grp.VoiceGroup.linesperagent.help3: 3. Predictive mode: Used as an initial value.
grp.VoiceGroup.maximumlinesperagent.help: The upper bound for the number of customers the dialer dials for a reserved agent when a campaign is running in predictive mode. Range is 1 to 100. Default is 2.
grp.VoiceGroup.abandoncalllimit.help: When enabled (abandonEnabled is set to true), you can set the abandoned calls limit for the percentage of abandoned calls in the campaign. When disabled (abandonEnabled is set to false), the campaign dials without regard to the abandon limit. Range is 1 to 100. The granularity is to one 10th of a percent. Default is 3.
grp.VoiceGroup.voicecalladjustment.help: A count of the number of live voice connections that must occur before the Dialer adjusts. Increasing this number results in less frequent adjustments based on larger sample size. Decreasing this number results in more frequent adjustments using a smaller sample size. Range is 10 to 5000. Default is 70
grp.VoiceGroup.predictivegain.help: The size of the adjustment to lines per agent each time an adjustment is made. Increasing this number results in larger lines per agent adjustments. Decreasing this number results in smaller lines per agent adjustments. Range is 0.1 to 3.0. Default is 0.1.
grp.VoiceGroup.noansweringlimit.help: The number of times the software allows a dialed phone number to ring. Range is from 2 to 10. Default is 4.
grp.VoiceGroup.maximumattempts.help: The maximum number of attempts, including callbacks and retries. Range is from 1 to 100. Default is 1.
grp.VoiceGroup.abandonedcallwaittime.hel: Minimum duration (in seconds) of an outbound call. If the outbound call is less than the specified value, Outbound Option considers the call to be customer abandoned and schedules the record for a retry. To disable this feature, set the parameter to 0. Range is 0 to 10. Default is 1.
grp.VoiceGroup.campaignprefixdigits.help: Digits to prefix to each customer number dialed from this campaign. Maximum length of 15 digits.
grp.VoiceGroup.personalizedcallback.help: If enabled, this parameter allows an agent to schedule a callback to a customer for a specific date and time. A personal callback connects the same agent who initiated the callback to the customer. True or false. Default is false.
grp.VoiceGroup.reschedulecallbackmode.he: Determines how Outbound Option handles a personal callback if the agent is not available. Default is useCampaignDN. Options are as follows:1.Use campaign DN 2.Same time next business day 3.Abandon
grp.VoiceGroup.noanswerdelay.help: The time (in minutes) that the software waits before calling back a no-answer call.Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 60.
grp.VoiceGroup.busysignaldelay.help: The time (in minutes) that the software waits before calling back a busy phone number. Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 60.
grp.VoiceGroup.customerabandoneddelay.he: If a customer abandons a call, the time (in minutes) that the Dialer waits before calling the customer back. Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 30.
grp.VoiceGroup.dialerabandoneddelay.help: If the Dialer abandons a call, the time (in minutes) that the Dialer waits before calling the customer back. Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 60.
grp.VoiceGroup.answeringmachinedelay.hel: If an answering machine answers a call, the time (in minutes) that the Dialer waits before calling the customer back. Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 60.
grp.VoiceGroup.customernothomedelay.help: If a customer is not home, the time (in minutes) that the Dialer waits before calling the customer back. Range is 1 to 99999. Default is 60.
grp.VoiceGroup.minimumsilenceperiod.help: The minimum silence period (in milliseconds) required to classify a call as voice detected. If many answering machine calls are being passed through to agents as voice, then increasing this value accounts for longer pauses in answering machine greetings. Range is from 100 to 1000. Default is 608.
grp.VoiceGroup.analysisperiod.help: The number of milliseconds spent analyzing this call. If there is a short agent greeting on an answering machine, then a longer value categorizes that answering machine call as voice. If the call is to a business where the operator has a longer scripted greeting, a shorter value categorizes the long, live greeting as an answering machine call. Range is from 1000 to 10000. Default is 2500.
grp.VoiceGroup.minimumvalidspeech.help: Minimum number of milliseconds of voice required to classify a call as voice detected. Range is 50 to 500. Default is 112.
grp.VoiceGroup.maximumanalysistime.help: The maximum number of milliseconds allowed for analysis before identifying a problem analysis as dead air/low volume. Range is 1000 to 10000. Default is 3000.
grp.VoiceGroup.maxterminationtoneanalysi: The maximum number of milliseconds the dialer analyzes an answering machine voice message looking for a termination tone. If the message has an odd tone and the analysis does not recognize it, the call is not transferred or dropped until this timeout occurs.Range is 1000 to 60000. Default is 30000.
grp.VoiceGroup.timerange.help: 1)Start Time:The time the campaign starts dialing customer numbers. The format for this parameter is hours:minutes. Range is from 00:00 to 23:59. The default value is taken from the Blended_Agent_Options table column values for DialStartHours and DialStartMinutes. 2)End Time:The time the campaign stops dialing customer numbers. The format for this parameter is hours:minutes. Range is from 00:00 to 23:59. The default value is taken from the Blended_Agent_Options table column values for DialEndHours and DialEndMinutes.
grp.VoiceGroup.campaignpurposetype.help: The type of campaign. Default is agentCampaign. The options are as follows:
grp.VoiceGroup.campaignpurposetype.help1: 1) Agent Campaign: This type of campaign uses an outbound mode that causes the Dialer to transfer every customer call associated with a specific skill group to an agent.
grp.VoiceGroup.campaignpurposetype.help2: 2) IVR Campaign: This type of campaign uses an outbound mode that causes the Dialer to transfer every customer call associated with a specific skill group to a service control-based IVR instead of an agent. This option allows a contact center to run unassisted outbound campaigns using prerecorded messages in the IVR.
grp.VoiceGroup.callprogressanalaysis.hel: A collection of parameters for Call Progress Analysis (CPA). Any combination of parameters within this collection can be set. If none of the parameters are provided and CPA is enabled for the campaign by default, CPA recording is set to false and default parameter values are set from the Blended_Agent_Options table.
grp.VoiceGroup.enableipamd.help: When set to false, CPA for all calls made from this Dialer is disabled on a campaign-by-campaign basis, including voice detection, fax/modem detection, and answering machine detection. True or false. Default is true.
grp.VoiceGroup.recordcpa.help: If enabled is set to true, you can specify this parameter. If you set it to true, the gateway provides a media stream and the Dialer records .wav files. True or false. Default is false.
grp.VoiceGroup.amdtreatmentmode.help: If enabled (ipAmdEnabled is set to true), when the Dialer detects an answering machine, it does one of the following:
grp.VoiceGroup.termainatetonedetect.help: When this parameter is set to true, the Dialer transfers the call after detecting the answering machine beep. True or false. Default is false.

grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Mi: The skill-level value for the minimum number of minutes before the outbound contacts can be retried. This value synchronizes with the General Skill Settings and can be superceded at the outcome level or by callback management.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ma: The skill-level value for the maximum number of times a contact may be tried (except if manually called by an agent).  This value sychronizes with the General Skill Settings and can be superceded at the outcome or phone number level.  Callbacks use a separate value for this field.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.De: This sets the time period that records will be stored on the virtual cluster.  After this time, expired records will be deleted from the virtual cluster but will still be available the data warehouse for reporting purposes.  With Proactive XS, an expired record will be checked into the CRM or other external system.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Co: The number of attempts that should be made to deliver a call for agent handling, before being considered for an inbound call.  This will diminish the ping-pong effect of priority blending.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.In: The minimum number of seconds that an agent will be retained to support outbound activity, before being released to take other work.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ma: The number of seconds that the phone will ring before being considered a 'no answer' by the system.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Be: When the abandon rate reaches this percentage of the target threshold amount, the system will begin to throttle the ratio being dialed to limit the number of abandoned calls. Example, the threshold is 3% and the value is 50, then the system would begin to dampen the aggressiveness of the pacing engine when the abandon rate reaches 1.50%
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ab: The cutoff value is subtracted from the abandon rate to determine when the system will call at a 1:1 ratio to limit the risk of having abandoned calls. Example: for a skill having a threshold of 3.00% and cutoff value of 0.2, 1:1 dialing ratio will be enforced when the calculated abandoned rate reaches 2.8%.

The targeted maximum percentage of abandoned calls allowed while running this skill, used along with the other governance settings to control the aggressiveness of the pacing engine.  The value is inherited from the Business Unit and can be adjusted for the skill if the 'Override BU abandon rate' field is enabled.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ma: The maximum allowed calls per waiting agent that can be dialed.  The system may deliver a lower number based on the  mathematical algorithm that is determining the maximum calls to dial to achieve the lowest wait time to receive another live call while not exceeding the various limits including abandon rate, defined by the user.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.En: The number of seconds the system will wait after receiving 0 records back from the calling list before notifying administrators and agents.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Pe: The percentage of agents that must be waiting before the system will allow more than one call per agent. The higher the percentage, the lower the chance of abandoned calls.  The default value for this setting is 25%.  For example, if 12 agents are logged in, 3 must be waiting before the system will dial more than one call for each agent.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Bl: If enabled, the system will retry contacts that have been called at least once.  If you wish to try a record just once, disable this option.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ov: If enabled, the abandon rate will be calculated based solely on activity in this skill instead of across the skills collectively in the Business Unit.  This will enable the user to configure a value higher or lower than the limit defined in the business unit configuration.
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.Ag: This setting determines the speed at which the system will ramp up to the maximum dialing ratio.
Conservative - normal speed; the recommended setting
Aggressive - maximum speed.  Not recommended except for a list with a reach rate of less than 10%
Caution:  settings above'Conservative' may cause the system to reach the maximum allowed abandon rate too quickly and cause the safety protocols to reach a 1:1 dialing mode.
grp.InContact.PriorityInitialPriority.mi: Priority Initial Priority cannot be lesser than 0
grp.InContact.PriorityInitialPriority.ma: Priority Initial Priority cannot be greater than 9999
grp.InContact.PriorityInitialPriority.re: Priority Initial Priority cannot be empty
grp.InContact.GeneralSettingsHelpText.lo: Enabled by default, this directs the system to load contacts that have previously been dispositioned as a callback.  Disabling this option will block delivery of records configured as callbacks.
